&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Associate Creative Director&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;London, Hybrid&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position sits in our &lt;strong&gt;Marketing &amp;amp; Technology&lt;/strong&gt; service based in London. We combine data, technology, creative and paid media to crack brands’ business problems &amp;amp; drive revenue through a variety of digital marketing solutions like social, influencer, TTL ad campaigns, augmented reality, AI and innovation. Our clients include eBay, easyJet, Just Eat Takeaway and Pepsico.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB PURPOSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Associate Creative Director for an exciting AI client of ours. The work we produce for them is varied and can range drastically from simple BAU creative responses, to in-person creative sprints and even full productions across multiple global markets. So, broad creative experience is required to ensure that whatever the brief, you feel comfortable leading the team and providing clear direction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a creative lead on the client, you will be responsible for ensuring creative excellence across all campaigns and projects. You will work with a wider team of creatives, designers, producers etc, providing clear, decisive feedback, guidance and inspiration to support members of the team across these disciplines. As well as building, delegating and empowering the team to confidently take on work, you will be a hands-on creative with a a willingness to ‘get your hands dirty’ to help the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Communication &amp;amp; presentation skills are critical due to frequent touchpoints with internal and external senior stakeholders in, both of which are located across the UK and US. You’ll be expected to work fast and nimble, getting work organised and ready to present to client. You will also attend and lead in-person creative sprints &amp;amp; workshops with the wider creative teams as well as the clients internal creative teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft brilliant, award winning ideas that capture attention and inspire our clients creatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create opportunities for account growth through selling brilliant creative campaigns that have community and culture at the heart of them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinking to lead your roster of clients to success through excellent creative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, develop, motivate and inspire DEPT’s creative teams and encourage collaboration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the accounts team to ensure a smooth monthly production process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Suggest best ways of working, and hustle for the best opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver and inspire innovative and high quality work across all deliverables from the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be aware of and respond to current advertising and media trends and pop culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use experience and ideas to contribute to the development of our creative process&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present work internally and externally to an excellent standard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up-to-date with industry developments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiate and facilitate creative team collaboration and sharing, and team cohesion through social and team building initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SKILLS AND PREVIOUS EXPERIENCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be an AI-native and have an interest in AI generally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategically minded with the ability to sell bigger ideas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be Figma-native (this is where we do 90% of our work/presentations)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep up to date with the latest tech/AI trends and have a broad understanding of the competitor landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong performance chops&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
